notes.note: Customer called to inquire about claims process. Walked him through process to have vehicle diagnosed and submit a claim. Was curios to know if he could take it to a Land Rover dealership. Informed him that he needs to go to an authorized repair facility, but if he called around to all the facilities local to him and no one is willing to work on the vehicle (Darren had issues with another client not being able to find a facility willing to work on his vehicle), that he could call back and inform us, and we would make a note on his file to note that we are willing to make an exception and have him go to the dealer. Informed him he will have to pay any labour overages above and beyond max hourly limit of $130. M.P.

notes.note: Customer called again, got more info on the Transmission concern. Customer purchased vehicle on Saturday May the 25th. May the 26th (Sunday) took the vehicle for a drive and started noticing transmission issues. Says the vehicle would tell him to pull over and put it in park. He would put it in park and try to drive, and the vehicle would shift automatically back into park. Called selling dealer on Monday May the 27th to report concern, and was told they did not notice the concern he is facing prior to selling him the vehicle, and that he needs to put a claim in through CGW. Informed the customer that we will not authorize a claim for him for this concern as it happened directly following purchasing the vehicle, and that he needs to reach out to the selling dealer to see if they can rectify the situation for him. M.P.
